The paper deals with the design of a channel shortener for a Viterbi equalizer in single-carrier systems. This involves optimizing the prefilter, target response, and feedback filter to maximize mutual information lower bound based on a mismatched detection model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques and analysis of information theoretical properties, which could also place it in the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the design of a receiver filter, which could also place it in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
